   JOINTLY-REPRESENTED PARTIES’

   Pursuant to Rules 26, 33, and 34 of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure and the Local
   Rules of this Court, Defendants J. David Oder, Rockledge, LLC, and JDOG, LLC (the “Jointly-
   Represented Parties”) hereby submit the following responses and objections to Plaintiff S4 Payments
   Inc.’s (“Shift4”) First Set of Interrogatories (“Interrogatories”) to Defendants J. David Oder,
   Rockledge, LLC, and JDOG, LLC.
   GENERAL OBJECTIONS
   The Jointly-Represented Parties object to each Interrogatory and the Instructions to the
   extent that it calls for information protected from disclosure by the attorney-client privilege, the work
   product doctrine, or any other applicable privilege, immunity, or right. The Jointly-Represented
   Parties will not produce privileged documents or information.
   The Jointly-Represented Parties object to the Instructions and each Interrogatory to the
   extent that it purports to impose any requirement or obligation greater than or inconsistent with the
   Federal Rules of Civil Procedure, the Local Rules of this Court, and the parties’ agreements.
   The production of any documents or information responsive to any of these Interrogatories
   shall not be deemed a waiver of the attorney-client privilege, the protection afforded to attorney
   work product, or any other applicable privilege with respect to any other documents or information
   relating to the same or any other subject matter. The Jointly-Represented Parties reserve any such
   privileges with respect to the production of documents or information responsive to any other
   discovery requests, notwithstanding the production of documents or information responsive to an
   Interrogatory.
   The Jointly-Represented Parties’ responses to these Interrogatories are based upon
   information reasonably available and known to them at this time. The Jointly-Represented Parties
   reserve the right to amend and/or supplement these responses as additional information becomes
   available through discovery, investigation, or otherwise.
